  "finger_focus": "Ring fingers reach up to W (above S) and O (above L)",
  "tips": [
    {
      "type": "lead",
      "text": "Two new letters today, and both go to the ring fingers - the ones that least want the job. W sits above S, O sits above L. You reach up, you strike, you come straight back. Mind the return as much as the reach; a finger left hanging up top is a typo waiting to happen."
    },
    {
      "type": "drop",
      "text": "Left ring finger lifts off S and taps W. Right ring finger lifts off L and taps O. The other seven fingers stay home on ASDF JKL; - they hold your place while the ring fingers go up and back. Don't tilt the whole hand; just the one finger travels."
    },
    {
      "type": "callout",
      "icon": "🖐",
      "title": "The weak finger sets the pace",
      "text": "The ring finger is the slowest of the four, and it will not be hurried. So don't try. Keep an even, unbothered rhythm and let it land cleanly each time. Speed is the one thing on this keyboard you never have to chase - it arrives on its own once the reach is clean."
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "kind": "drill",
      "unit": "w",
      "baseReps": 20,
      "keys": ["w"],
      "target": "w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w w",
      "finger": "orange",
      "title": "The letter W",
      "hint": "Left ring finger reaches up from S to W, then straight back. Space after each."
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "kind": "drill",
      "unit": "o",
      "baseReps": 20,
      "keys": ["o"],
      "target": "o o o o o o o o o o o o o o o o o o o o",
      "finger": "orange",
      "title": "The letter O",
      "hint": "Right ring finger reaches up from L to O, then straight back. Space after each."
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "kind": "drill",
      "unit": "wo ow",
      "baseReps": 7,
      "keys": ["w", "o"],
      "target": "wo ow wo ow wo ow wo ow wo ow wo ow wo ow",
      "finger": "orange",
      "title": "Both rings",
      "hint": "Alternate the two ring fingers: W up on the left, O up on the right."
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "text": "Both rings are awake now, so let's set them to work. O is one of the busiest letters in the language - you will meet it in nearly every line you ever write, so it pays to make peace with it early. Read each word whole, then type it without glancing down."
    },
    {
